  "text": "Let us recall the idea from [CITATION_1] to construct division-interpolation formulas. Given a generically exact complex like (2.6) in Ω ⊂ C n and z ∈ Ω one can locally find a tuple H = (H ℓ k ), where H ℓ k is a smooth form-valued section of Hom (E k,ζ , E ℓ,z ), such that H ℓ k = 0 for k < ℓ, H ℓ ℓ = I E ℓ when ζ = z, and in general (2.11)",
